  "text": "Another recent example in favour of torus instability was provided by a data-driven zero-β simulation in [CITATION_1] . There, the MHD evolution of active region 11123 from November 2010 was reproduced numerically, using both vector magnetic field HMI data and a derived vector velocity field in a spatiotemporally evolving bottom boundary. The model provided insight in the various phases of the flux rope eruption: a gradual rise resulting from magnetic reconfigurations in its vicinity preceded a changeover where the flux rope starts to rise at several tens of km/s. Analysing the instantaneous decay index above the rising flux rope, the changeover from slow to fast rise and ejection was found consistent with the critical index crossing.",
